5) May 11 is our one-year anniversary. The day we first talked to each other. (*sigh*) I still love him.

I'm not delusional.
I am quite the opposite of a realist.
Because reality is whatever you want it to be.
If you allow it.

Most of the world acts outside-in.
I act inside-out.
Inside-out isn't wrong.
It's comfy.

I've decided to go on and participate in the Day of Silence.
'Cause being LGBTQ isn't wrong.
Fuck whatever my parents think.

So, Tuesday night (Opening Night @ Camden Yards) me and my dad went to the game. I took the Light Rail for the first time that I can remember. (My VERY first game was when I was 6 and I don't remember much. I DO still have the magazine from that game, though.)

Anyway, we got there early for batting practice. Not too early, as the O's were already done and the Tigers were practicing. The COOLEST thing is... wait for it... I caught NOT ONE, BUT TWO batting practice balls! I kept the first and gave the second to a VERY cute little boy standing next to me. Well... the first one Fernando Rodney threw in my general direction. But the second one WAS hit directly to me. (I also realize that the ball would've hit me in the face if I didn't have my glove up. The key to catching batting practice balls: keep the hands in front of the face.) And someone congratulated me on catching two balls in one batting practice. That was pretty cool.

That was awesome. However, we ("we" being the O's) lost 3-1. But we've sorta rebounded since then. Took two from the Royals. Nick Markakis hit his first GRAND SLAM. That was awesome. We're 5-6 now. Still in 4th, but only half a game behind the Yankees for 3rd!

-Arrogant Oriole

O's won the first game at Camden Yards!! (Final: O's 6, Tigers 2) As of now, we're 3-4 and 4th in the division. Division standings don't really matter until late July. I just like including them.

I'm likely going to tomorrow's game. Opening Night! Can't wait.

As most people know, Cory Lidle and his instructor tragically had their lives cut short last week in a plane crash.

Even though he was a Yankee, I don't REALLY want anyone to die ever. It's even sadder when you consider that the thing he loved was the thing that took him away from us.

I remember that one of the games the Orioles won (final: 9-4) when we went was on September 8. It was Lidle against Bedard. I went with my then-new friend Chelsea, a Yankee fan. I still have the scorecard, magazine, and ticket from that game. Now that Lidle is gone, I put it on my bulletin board. I think I'll put "R.I.P. Cory Lidle 1972-2006" on it.

I think that "Wake Me Up When September Ends" is like a theme song for any sadness that happens in my lifetime. For me. On sad annivversaries, days of death, whenever it rains, and just when I'm feeling down, I play it.

I hope his family feels better after this tragedy.

"They say that whenever a bell rings, an angel gets his wings. I think that whenever there's a light breeze, a ghost goes into the light."- Me

Stay strong.
-Arrogant Oriole

I was in 4th grade, during math class. My teacher had told us that there was a terrorist attack and that school was closing early (as every other school in Maryland). Being 8 years old, I didn't really realize the importance of the day. As time went by, I realized that the day was a very important day and that almost 3000 people had died because of the cruel decision of one group. The day also changed me in a way. I don't really feel safe getting on a plane anymore, and I've grown a little more mature.

Lesson for today:
Take the time to say "I love you" to the ones you love. It could be the last time you do. You never know.

*WE WILL NEVER FORGET*

-Arrogant Oriole

P.S. My current song kinda fits, doesn't it?
http://arrogant-oriole.livejournal.com/2831.html

I went to the Orioles game today with my dad. Every time we've been to the Yard this year, we lost (We're 0-4). We sat in section 66, an upgrade from section 67 by that nice usher. I always seem to meet nice ushers.

Anyway, Erik Bedard pitched well. 11 hits given up, but all but one were singles. He kept us in the game, so hats off to you, Bedard.

Drama in the 9th: Tied 2-2. 1 out. Corey Patterson stole second. Ramon Hernandez with a 3-2 count. CAN HE DELIVER A GAME WINNING HIT?!?! YES, BUT DOES HE?!?!?!?!?!?!

Shot up the middle. Patterson scores easily. Orioles win 3-2. (Now me and my dad are 1-4 on the year.)

I even got a souveneir. A cup. Useful.

Thoughts:
1. After we won, I high-fived a whole bunch of people I didn't know. Yeah. Dramatic wins will do that to you.
2. I like "Psych." Anyone else like "Psych?" Shawn Spencer is CUTE!
3. Pluto is no longer considered a planet. I don't know what to believe anymore.
4. Why does Brian Callen remind me of Jay Gibbons so much?

No poem this time. My brain is suffocating over the lack of AC.

-Arrogant Oriole

It's been a while since I've updated this think. Well, if you're expecting a good update, you'll be disappointed. As you can see by my avatar (who has NOTHING to do with airbending), je suis malade. Figure it out.

Thoughts
1. Bonus Stage isn't ending at all! (Or is it...?)
2. First Orioles exhibition game is next (or should I say this) week. You know I'm gonna listen to it. Or watch it. Or maybe you don't know...
3. I plan to post my semi-decent drawings on my LJ. I'll get better at it.
4. I'm a semi-finalist in a national poetry contest. Cool!
5. I had a dream where ALMOST EVERYONE around me was pregnant. That was weird. I was at an Arrogant Worms event... and THEY were pregnant too... in fact, Trevor went into labor during their performance... creepy... sorry I forced that on you.
6. Due to Thought #5, I am now writing a song about pregnancy. It's to the tune of "The Last Saskatchewan Pirate," so you'll never hear it. But I might post the lyrics when I'm done.

And now, Arrogant Oriole's Poetry Corner (Another reference...)

Title: Anticipation

My teacher...
  Is droning on...
    As the clock is stuck
      At 2:57 pm...
        Just 3 more minutes...
          And I'll be free (for a week)...
            The minute hand...
              Trudges to 2:58 pm...
                I can tell...
                  That my teacher...
                    Doesn't want to be here, either...
                      2:59 pm...
                        60 lousy seconds...
                          Between me...
                            And freedom...
                              2:59:37 pm...
                                We all count the seconds...
                                  As the second hand...
                                    Teases us...
                                      2:59:57...
                                        3...
                                          2...
                                            1...
"Have a good winter break class!!"
My teacher says
as we rush out the door
I swear
he hated waiting more than we did...

Poem
Driving down the highway
Of Allegheny County
I saw a strange man
with orange eyes like fire
He wore a green art smock
and wobbled and swayed
I thought he was drunk
and maybe he was
But I saw him again
and now I know

It's not a quiz, but I thought it was funny. I am from Maryland.
You Know You're From Maryland When...
You know more than 10 people who own boats and they all park them at the same marina in Annapolis You can pronounce and spell "Pocomoke," "Mattaponi," "Accokeek," and "Havre de Grace" You prononce "Bowie" BOO-ie not BOW-ie or BAUW-ie 1 hour is an easy commute to work You have more than three recipies for crabcakes French fries just don't taste right without Old Bay There are more than two crab places in your town Even your high school cafeteria made good crabcakes You got your first lacrosse stick before you were six years old You call all turtles "terrapins" You refer to your state as "Merlind" Your mother shops at Hecht's You still call Six Flags America "Adventure World", or even "Wild World" You still remember the Wild World commercial (Wild World's the cure for the summertime blues!) You can tell the difference between the smells of septic and marsh. You not only know how to eat hard crabs but you also know how to catch them, cook them and tell the males from the females. You don't think that Assawoman Bay is a strange name for a body of water. You know perfectly well why Rehoboth is called "Little San Francisco" M R Ducks makes perfect sense. So does C M Wangs. You think Salisbury is a big city. You think of dumplings as wet slippery squares of boiled dough. You and your boss take off of work when the fish are running or the ducks are flying in. You've eaten muskrat at a church dinner but think it's better the way you fix it. You think of "Dairy Queen" as a pageant title and not a place to get an ice cream. "Formal wear" is a ball cap, a flannel shirt and Timberlands. You still root for the Orioles even when they suck You'll never understand why tourists come to DC. When in Florida, you can only laugh when you see signs saying "Real Maryland Blue Crab Cakes!" You color with "Crowns", take a "Share" with "Wooter" and think the president lives in "Warshenton." You know the difference between Glen Burnie ghetto and Catonsville ghetto. Your whole family lives within a 200 mile radius of your town. Dale Earnhardt's accident was a close personal loss to your father At least one man in your family is a waterman You plan for "The Festival" a year in advance. During the summer, you spend more time in Ocean City than at home. Margret Heater, Hedspace, Jepetto, Outside Joke and Mary Prankster are people you think are "Famous" Your radio dial is stuck on 99.1 You actually get these jokes and pass them on to other friends from Maryland.


Get Your Own "You Know You're From" Meme Here

And now, a poem for you all. I made it up just now.

The light breeze blows in from the window
And whisks me away from the world
It carries me beyond the street
Beyond the neighborhood
Beyond the city
The state
The country
Beyond the world
It carries me out to sea
Where I look down
I float but never fall
I dream but never sleep
I wonder but never think...

Signing off, Arrogant Oriole
